messages.text:
Hey folks :alert2:

We are kicking off the July Capitalisation reporting, please remember our new process:
1. Infer the time spent per 2025 Key Results (KRs) and type of activity per person.
2. Report as much time as possible _but_ only time worked on KRs and https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Ljgaq-J76NIMVAYRLBdHQ1Onx94onjCv-gjQRXtYc10/edit?tab=t.tv0vf7sxjp0s#bookmark=id.ggmesfqo2k9.
Let us know if there are other activities your team is working on that should be added to the list.
1. Take this opportunity to reduce overhead, placing reporting at higher management levels (i.e. tribe level). 
2. The sources of truth for reporting are:
    a. *Workday* - cutoff date is July-31 10AM Berlin
    b. *https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/u/0/d/1jdRyu6eoWAyossWaGCbXEu_rrmuxWWRWni5Mzy2FLBM/edit* 
3. https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1sAXkYRJ9E-0UDtT7qvi_GBCF3v-bbS8wGRihtLQkO7Y/edit?gid=1125151938#gid=1125151938 within the timeline
*Reporting starts:* Friday, 1st August (today)
 *Deadline:* Thursday, 7th August EOD (Berlin time)

Hey folks on the above :upvote: *new tab added: Public Demo Signups:* https://docs.google.com/document/d/1w_XOLs9WPoFBbz3GNjOxDpXGYVGlq7noplV26ZILCEU/edit?usp=sharing

• *Problem:* We sometimes have limited visibility into how end up in the public demo prioritization, resulting in multiple topics coming together and the need to prioritize even internally what will be presented publicly. 
• *Solution:* Strategize our demo plans so that the team ALWAYS has a public presentation *NOT* a recording going forward
• *Ask:* as part of the weekly notes/standup prep - add topics that *have been or are planned to be submitted for certain calendar weeks.* 
• *Outcome: @UEZ4PRFKM* *@U03TY4YJU4X* to work with Felix on the portfolio team to make sure we are above the line for the presentation.
